quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  25,33,"And no example or parable do they bring, but We reveal to you the truth, and the better explanation thereof"
  25,34,"Those who will be gathered to Hell on their faces, such will be in an evil state, and most astray from the path"
  25,35,"And indeed We gave Musa the Scripture, and placed his brother Harun with him as a helper"
  25,36,"And We said: \"Go you both to the people who have denied Our Ayat.\" Then We destroyed them with utter destruction"
  25,37,"And Nuh's people, when they denied the Messengers, We drowned them, and We made them as a sign for mankind. And We have prepared a painful torment for the wrongdoers"
  25,38,"And (also) `Ad and Thamud, and the Dwellers of Ar-Rass, and many generations in between"
  25,39,"And for each We put forward examples, and each We brought to utter ruin"
  25,40,And indeed they have passed by the town on which was rained the evil rain. Did they not then see it Nay! But they used not to expect any resurrection
  25,41,"And when they see you, they treat you only in mockery (saying): \"Is this the one whom Allah has sent as a Messenger"
  25,42,"He would have nearly misled us from our gods, had it not been that we were patient and constant in their worship!\" And they will know, when they see the torment, who it is that is most astray from the path"
  25,43,Have you seen him who has taken as his god his own vain desire Would you then be a guardian over him